1991 / 9 / 7 / 23 / 9 / 146
1992 / 0 / 3 / -- / 4 / 11
1993 / 0 / 20
1994 / 0 / 2 / 2 / 8 / 70
1995 / 0 / 1 / 1 / 1 / 1
1996 / 0 / 13 / 46
1997 / 1 / 4 / 4 / 11 / 44
1998 / 1 / 9 / 14 / 3 / 3
1999 / 0 / 3 / 3 / 3 / 5
2000 / 0 / 2 / 2 / 6 / 13
2001 / 0 / 1 / 1 / 2 / 8
2002 / 0
2003 / 0
2004 / -- / -- / 54 / -- / 11
Notes:
1. 1996 - Included 12 outbreaks of bovine anthrax in Sardinia
2. 1997 - Outbreaks of bovine anthrax in Basilicata, Lazio, Sicily,
Campanna, Sardinia, Calabria and Puglia
3. 1998 - Outbreaks of bovine anthrax in Calabria, Basilicata, Umbria, and
Veneto regions
4. 2004 - Outbreaks of bovine anthrax in Basilicata
5. One outbreak of swine anthrax (1 case) was reported in 1990; 0 in 1997;
1 (in Basilicata) in 2004.
6. 4 infected red deer were reported in Basilicata during 2004.
Notable outbreaks:
1975 to 1977 - Outbreaks in Milan were associated with processing imported
animal hides from Africa. [1]
1992 (publication year) - An outbreak (3 cases) of cutaneous anthrax among
members of a family was associated with an infected cow. [2]
References:
1. Gelosa L. Malignant pustule in province of Milan, Italy. Ann Slavo 1978;
20:907-919
2. de Lalla F, et al. Familial outbreak of agricultural anthrax in an area
of northern Italy. Eur J Clin Microbiolol Infect Dis 1992; 11:839-842
